    "caption": "The river's most enthusiastic tool user — and the hand-holdingest sleeper.",
    "shortDescription": "Sea otters float on their backs in kelp forests, cracking open mussels and clams with a rock balanced on their chest like a tiny picnic table. They each have a favorite rock they tuck into a fold of loose skin under their arm, carrying it from meal to meal. Fun fact: Sea otters hold hands while they sleep so the current doesn't carry them apart — a group of sleeping otters is called a raft."
